******
[2] Queensland Government official statement
Date: Fri 6 Jan 2012
Source: Queensland Government Primary Industries and Fisheries [edited]
http://www.dpi.qld.gov.au/4790_2900.htm


Current situation - New Hendra virus case in Townsville area
------------------------
A deceased horse on a property in the Townsville area has returned a positive test result for Hendra virus infection.

The horse had shown rapid onset of illness and died on [Tue 3 Jan 2012]. A positive result for the virus arrived late [Wed 4 Jan 2012].

Biosecurity Queensland is in the process of quarantining this property and will test and monitor the other horses at this location over the next month.

Hendra virus is a notifiable disease. If you suspect Hendra virus, please contact Biosecurity Queensland immediately on 13 25 23 or the Emergency Disease Watch Hotline on 1800 675 888.

