[This is a vicious disease for horses and people. When flying foxes are in the area, horses should be kept out from under trees, especially at times when the foxes feed on the fruit. Horse owners need to critically access the property to determine safe places for the horses.

It is sad that this disease still seems to march on. It may have started last calendar year, but it feels like one long single year of Hendra virus.

Townsend in Queensland may be found at: http://healthmap.org/r/1BYq. - Mod.TG]
